What's Been Correctly Implemented:
-----------------------------------------
Hopefully all of it


Departures from recommended calling convention:
-----------------------------------------
We don't have really any departures from the recommended calling convention.


How we implemented print module:
-----------------------------------------
We implemented the print module as outlined by the specs. We accounted 
for edge cases seperatly and printed character out by recusivly itterating down 
each digit. 


How we're representing RPN character's value stack:
-----------------------------------------
We are representing the value stack by using a 10,000 word stack that r2
points to, and we have r3 consistently track the amount of values currently
on that stack.


List of Sections:
-----------------------------------------
init
- Contains code to initialize our jump tables, register 0, and the stack
pointer as well as containing callmain.

text
- Contains all our code for the printd module and our calculator-related
functions.

data 
- Reserves 10,000 words of space on our stack.

rodata
- Reserves space for our jump tables. (here lies data for our jumptables)


